        children: "The art of journal keeping, letter writing and daily diary entries are becoming extinct as methods of memory management are changing in today's technology driven world. What once was detailed on paper with memory fresh at hand is now posted on YouTube Today, blogs replace diary entries. Hand-written letters to loved ones are far slower than a quick Facebook 'poke' or a cell phone text message."
